-width="1920" data-npf='{"type":"video","provider":"tumblr","url":"https://va.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_720.mp4","media":{"url":"https://va.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_720.mp4","type":"video/mp4","width":1920,"height":1920},"poster":[{"url":"https://64.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_frame1.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","width":1920,"height":1920}],"filmstrip":{"url":"https://64.media.tumblr.com/previews/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_filmstrip.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","width":2000,"height":200}}'&gt;&lt;video controls="controls" autoplay="autoplay" playsinline="playsinline" muted="muted" poster="https://64.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_frame1.jpg"&gt;&lt;source src="https://va.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_qwqhqjrX1n1yphg3y_720.mp4" type="video/mp4"&gt;&lt;/source&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p&gt;Quite a few weeks ago one of my team-mates spotted me out a shrub on the sidelines of our field. These otherwise thorny menaces which had caused god-knows-how-many bleeding scratches on my ankle when we were busy stomping around the field, kicking around a ball, suddenly seemed like an alien being amidst usual life. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a child I had read about the touch-me-nots or &lt;i&gt;lojjaboti &lt;/i&gt;(Bengali) but cared to finally notice one after all these years. Fascinating! &amp;ldquo;I didn&amp;rsquo;t expect it to be so animal-like&amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo; was my first reaction as I watched the tiny leaves shrivel up, up and a little bit more, almost like a worm. It&amp;rsquo;s bright purplish crimson stems seemed as if blood flowed through them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I spent a good ten minutes or so, paying the touch-me-nots the much deserved attention but spent longer —procrastinating— penning it down on pixels.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.ayanchoudhury.in/post/657566890094395392</link><guid>https://blog.ayanchoudhury.in/post/657566890094395392</guid><pubDate>Sat, 24 Jul 2021 11:00:54 +0530</pubDate><category>sketchbook</category><category>storytime</category><category>animation</category></item><item><title>The romantic concept of playing football in the rain has quite a lot of fanfare and I absolutely&amp;hellip;</title><description>&lt;div class="npf_row"&gt;&lt;figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="720" data-orig-width="1280"&gt;&lt;img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s640x960/375318b4427743791ccb38a88cbbf05582138832.jpg" data-orig-height="720" data-orig-width="1280" srcset="https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s75x75_c1/d9a506106e6df8b243615b05437dba239d61b22e.jpg 75w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s100x200/54c5a614501841bf77508d2c9bcf88bd9cf1e3c9.jpg 100w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s250x400/2e58f336277d515867dcc5fe645dcce402acc000.jpg 250w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s400x600/4180617202a820e2a0bd2f44b1409957fb53a7f7.jpg 400w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s500x750/8b1c93da917d0b5eaaf08beff49f4608a1cc649f.jpg 500w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s540x810/acc0c7abec37a8b4dea5e5e795660222aad746b2.jpg 540w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s640x960/375318b4427743791ccb38a88cbbf05582138832.jpg 640w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/01d91d532ed7762e88be9a6221f2b168/4d98e88049252f0c-aa/s1280x1920/705efee49b683c9d8fcb35981fbe2b93d611930a.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"/&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The romantic concept of playing football in the rain has quite a lot of fanfare and I absolutely don&amp;rsquo;t get the appeal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Speaking from experience, you can count your lucky stars if match day is on a breezy overcast day — easy on the players, easy on the spectators. Add a drizzle to that and things are still under control. Your boots are wet and you start feeling the chill but it&amp;rsquo;s all fine. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, once the heaven&amp;rsquo;s diapers start to overflow, it&amp;rsquo;s time to run. The wet ground grabs onto the ball and dribbling becomes impossible, people slip and fall all the time often injuring others, there&amp;rsquo;s water in your eyes, the wet sand on the ball bruises your skin, every shot on the ball kicks up the muddy water from the field (into your mouth), people splash each other with water and stop taking the game seriously, they jubilantly celebrate missed shots by sliding into the pool of water, the concept of opponents has long dissolved into the same muddy water, everyone&amp;rsquo;s laughing their asses off, the field quickly becomes a podium of slapstick humor, all the actors enjoying the dazzling absurd, chaotic experience under dark grey clouds. All of a sudden. A blinding bolt of lightning brings play to a halt. The deafening thunder follows. The clouds above have had the last laugh.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.ayanchoudhury.in/post/655119231002787840</link><guid>https://blog.ayanchoudhury.in/post/655119231002787840</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Jun 2021 10:36:24 +0530</pubDate><category>sketchbook</category><category>football</category><category>illustration</category><category>durgapur</category></item><item><title>Every time I would step on to the Force Traveller back in college, I&amp;rsquo;d heave a sigh of relief. The&amp;hellip;</title><description>&lt;div class="npf_row"&gt;&lt;figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="1500" data-orig-width="2000"&gt;&lt;img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/3ebda500542c0a2c263b890e9f6855cf/42eecd6f23472a74-5f/s640x960/3852958102d40947834a9751b5f9baf481d1cfe0.jpg" data-orig-height="1500" data-orig-width="2000" srcset="https://64.media.tumblr.com/3ebda500542c0a2c263b890e9f6855cf/42e